#1. Le Repas Frugal                             
##貧しき食事

Pablo Picasso,
1904

Le Repas frugal, created between Picasso's melancholic Blue Period and Rose Period, is one of his earliest forays into the technique of engraving. The sense of despondency and isolation is typical of his work at this time. It belongs to the La Suite des Saltimbanques, a series of fifteen etchings and drypoints made between 1904 and 1905.

                                                                                                         
                                                                                       

#####Designed by 721Land

An independent music label started in 2018, based in Shanghai, China. We do multi-style release, music event and communication & education project “Eating Music Camp”. We aim to discover fresh idea & passion on variety of music styles and build a good connection with music & life. Eating Music will always be open to the artists who is ready to define a new scene of Chinese independent music in future.

11. La famille de Saltimbanques au Macaque
サルタンバンクの家族と猿

#“Every act of creation is, first of all, an act of destruction.” 
##——Picasso 

As one of the greatest and most prolific artists in the world ever, and most famed for his creation of Cubism together with Georges Braque, Picasso also exerted influence on surrealism, neoclassicism and expressionism, and even on etching and drypoint commonly seen today. 

La Suite des Saltimbanques was created between his Blue Period (1901-1904) and Rose Period(1904–1906). In 1904 at the age of 23, he finished the best-known Le Repas frugal of the series. To people's astonishment, it was only his second try of etching. This monumental portrait of human suffering and isolation, borne with dignity in the face of life's hardships, has become an icon of Picasso's Blue Period. 

Being ranked as one of the greatest series of prints he has ever made, La Suite des Saltimbanques includes 15 pieces, which depict the offstage moments of Gypsies and acrobats including rehearsals, dinner with family, and bathing. 

We'd like to extend our sincere gratitude to Mr. Hikonobu Ise for sharing the treasures he collected. And we got something really exciting to announce soon, just stay tuned.
